  "task": "Create, validate, persist, and query JSON-LD SeVoNodes under adversarial, resource-constrained, and Byzantine fault conditions. Must handle all v4 requirements plus: (1) content-addressable storage — node @id must be derived from a SHA-256 hash of canonical node content (excluding @id and timestamp); duplicate content with different @ids must be detected and rejected, identical resubmissions must be idempotent; (2) causal ordering — every node carries a vector clock; writes must be rejected if they would violate causal consistency (e.g. a SelectionNode referencing a FitnessNode whose vector clock is not yet observed); queries must return results in causal order, not timestamp order; (3) Byzantine scorer detection — given a set of FitnessNodes where up to f of 3f+1 scorers may report fabricated EQS values, identify and exclude Byzantine scores using a BFT consensus protocol before computing aggregate fitness; (4) incremental index maintenance — maintain a secondary index on agent lineage and fitness ranges that updates in O(log n) per write, not rebuilt from scratch; multi-hop traversals ('all agents within k generations of X with EQS > threshold') must use the index and complete in under 10ms for 2000+ nodes; (5) snapshot isolation — concurrent read transactions must see a consistent point-in-time snapshot even while writes are in progress; demonstrate by interleaving 50 concurrent readers with 10 concurrent writers and verifying no reader sees a partial batch; (6) compaction without deletion — implement log-structured merge compaction that reduces storage by coalescing superseded nodes into summary nodes while preserving full auditability; original nodes remain accessible via content hash but are moved to a cold tier; (7) adversarial graph poisoning — detect and quarantine subgraphs where an injected node attempts to falsify lineage by claiming a parent that would alter selection history; verify Merkle proof of lineage integrity back to genesis node; (8) memory budget reduced to 48MB for all operations on a 2000-node graph",
  "scoringLogic": "correctness(0.10) + typeSafety(0.08) + schemaValidation(0.06) + concurrency(0.06) + referenceIntegrity(0.06) + cycleDetection(0.05) + schemaMigration(0.05) + crashRecovery(0.08) + contentAddressing(0.08) + causalOrdering(0.08) + byzantineDetection(0.08) + indexPerformance(0.06) + snapshotIsolation(0.06) + compaction(0.05) + lineageIntegrity(0.05) + memoryEfficiency(0.05) + adversarialRejection(0.03)",
